First off, it should be a felony to list fast food restaurants that are located inside malls/other establishments on google maps. Its not fast food if I have to get out of the car and go into a building.  I was driving across country for 20 hours and wanted to make a quick breakfast stop to grab a chicken breakfast burrito. After being directed to 2 different chick-fil-a's (located in the airport and the university) I finally chose the 49 W Maryland location. When I arrived I was livid to find out it was located in the mall. I decided to park and go inside because I was sick of driving around.  Chick-fil-a was located on the 3rd floor of the mall with no signs showing where to go. (I had to ask a cinnabon worker to point me in the right direction) I walk up to the counter and order 2 chicken breakfast burritos only to be told they don't have them. The cashier did not explain if they ran out or don't even serve them at their location. She was very rude compared to other Chick-fil-a workers I have interacted with. I then ordered 2 chicken biscuits that were god awful dry. I wasted an hour of my time to choke down the worst breakfast I've ever had. Thank god I don't live in this awful city.  Conclusion: Who ever listed this location on google maps as fast food should be given the death penalty.

The food is okay, not super great, but the chicken is decently flavored. The chicken strips were very small. The waffle fries have no flavor to them at all, except for the sharp taste of table salt. The frosted caramel coffee is okay, it has a nice creamy coffee flavor, but the caramel flavoring is a little bitter and has a slight after taste. The chick fil a sauce is good, and the ranch sauce is slightly better than average. Their honey mustard sauce is spicy and a little sharp, but all around good. Aside from the size, it is decent food for a decent price, but if you're hungry you likely wont be full up on one order of chicken strips and fries. Service was professional, friendly, and fast. The cashier was nice, clarified the order, and processed it quickly. The food was ready to take 2 minutes after paying. Quick, friendly service.

Do not come here if you have any allergy/food requirements - If I could give this location zero stars I would. I made a mobile order for a southwest salad with no chicken, no tortillas, and no cheese - I am very allergic to dairy and other stores accommodate this perfectly fine. I pick up my salad and it is covered in cheese, so I go back and apologize but request a new salad, even offering to pay again - the Manager made me prove my mobile order and was a little off-standing, but I get it, things happen, people make mistakes. I HATE being that guy who send back food but I also don't want my intestines to explode in the middle of the mall, right? He begrudgingly replaced my salad and when I open this one, the beans, corn, and peppers are frozen solid. Please note, this is the THIRD time I have received a frozen salad from this location - see picture of ice encrusted salad attached. The managers were lackadaisical and rude when I let them know and sent me away with a frozen salad, asking "well did you at least get your fork and knife?" as if to joke about how poor the experience was. This store is an embarrassment to the Chick-fil-a franchise and the management is a joke. Save yourself the time and money and go anywhere else.
